{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend Maternity / Shared Parental Leave from 12 months to 15 months",
        "additional_details": "Extending unpaid leave could: \r\n- Give another choice other than leaving employment or returning before ready\r\n- Encourage fathers to take shared parental leave\r\n- Provide job security, for example if a partner faced possible redundancy\r\n- Enable mothers to start their leave before the birth without losing time after\r\n- Give the right to request additional unpaid leave, especially relevant if the parent must return due to Occupational Maternity Pay requirements.",
        "background": "Returning to work after maternity can be a hard and difficult experience. Extending the period of unpaid leave from 3 months to 6 months after SM Pay ends could help overcome the difficulties of new caring responsibilities, sleepless nights, breastfeeding, changed body and separation anxiety.",
